H3.text: Which UK city is traditionally associated with jute, jam and journalism. Dundee

A4.text: This, along with its other major industries, gave Dundee its epithet as the city of 'jute, jam and journalism'.

A5.text: Rapid expansion was brought on by the Industrial Revolution, particularly in the 19th century when Dundee was the centre of the global jute industry.
